    "prompt": "**VLIW scheduling.** Port the loop below to a **5-operation VLIW** machine and schedule **one iteration** with **as-soon-as-possible (ASAP)** scheduling — no software pipelining, no loop unrolling, no modifying the loop indexes.\n\nFunctional units (all fully pipelined): **1 Integer ALU (1cc)**, **2 Memory Units (MEM1, MEM2; 3cc)**, **1 FP-SUM (3cc)**, **1 FP-MUL (5cc)**. Latency = the result is usable that many cycles after issue.\n\n**P1.A** Fill the schedule grid: put each instruction in its issue-cycle row, under the column of the **specific unit** it uses. (Convention: when several identical units are free, use the lower-numbered one first — so two loads issued together go to MEM1 then MEM2.)\n**P1.B** Compute FLOPs/CC.\n**P1.C** If you unroll by 2 and the FP-MUL can also do SUM (3cc), how is performance affected?",
